@natashaj7 re: ImportActivity.java:90-101: you're totally right! it was dead code in ImportActivity so I deleted it there.

@PatrickDale re: TxcPortingUtility.java:211: yeah, thanks, it should be.

@natashaj7 re: separating classes into their own files. In general, I've always been told that, if a class exists only to serve another class (like ExportTask and the click handlers), it's good practice to make it a subclass so that the parent class is as self-contained as it can be. For some of the subclasses (the Import/ExportException classes), I went too far, so I've pulled them out into their own classes. For the others though, are you ok with keeping them as subclasses, at least until/unless we have to separate them out for testing reasons?

Related to that: now that it's getting a little bigger, do either of you have any preferences about package structure? I thought it might make sense to at least set up a "data" subpackage or something like that to hold the database classes and TxcPortingUtility (and related exceptions), so they'd be separated from the UI code. (I could do that separately later though, if moving the DbManager and Dictionary classes would inconvenience you with the text display changes. No reason to hurry.)
